# [SRV6OPS](../wg/srv6ops.html)

## Summary

The SRV6OPS Working Group session at IETF 126 featured key deployment updates, technical progress on active working group documents, and several new proposals. Operators including Deutsche Telekom and China Telecom shared their real-world strategies and experiences migrating legacy MPLS networks to SRv6. The session also covered implementations of SRv6 in open-source platforms (SONiC), address planning recommendations, and emerging use cases such as SRv6 in AI backends, end-to-end data center (DC) frontends, Service Function Chaining (SFC), and IPsec ESP-protected services.

